{"cursor":"6262","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"  {|{{Infobox Aircraft Begin |name = US-2 |logo = \n|image = US-1A-KAI-Flying boat01.jpg |caption = The second production US-2\n}}{{Infobox Aircraft Type |type = Air-sea rescue amphibian |manufacturer =\nShinMaywa |designer =  |first flight = 18 December 2003 |introduction = 30 March 2007 |retired =\n|status = in production |primary user = Japan Maritime Self Defense Force |more\nusers = |produced = 2003-Present |number built = 4 (3 expected) |unit cost =\n|developed from = ShinMaywa US-1A |variants with their own articles = }}\n|}\n\n\n\nThe '[[ShinMaywa]]' (formerly Shin Meiwa) 'US-2' is a Japanese large STOL\namphibious aircraft designed for air-sea rescue (SAR) work. The aircraft is\ncurrently operated by the 31st Fleet Air Wing (71st Air Force, 71st Flight\nSquadron) at Iwakuni air base and Atsugi air base. The US-2 is scheduled to\nreplace the older ShinMaywa US-1\n\nIn 2012, the US-2 is being introduced to the Indian Navy to enhance its search\nand rescue capabilities with no word yet if they will accept the\naircraft. In May 2013, two sides decided to establish a Joint Working\nGroup to explore the modality for the cooperation.\n","linknr":187,"url":"ShinMaywa_US-2","recorded":1375087302,"links":["/w/index.php?title=ShinMaywa_US-2&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=ShinMaywa_US-2&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bi